There is a (essentially pattern-terminological) reinterpretation in Kontsevich-Rosenberg, _Noncommutative spaces_, 6.8.1:

Let $M_v'$ be the family of canonical injections of valuation rings to their fields of fractions, and let $M_v$ be its image in the category of functors $CRing\to Set$. Consider schemes as covariant presheaves on $CRing$. Then a morphism $f:X\to Y$ of schemes is [[separated morphism of schemes|separated]] iff it is formally $M_v$-unramified, [[universally closed morphism|universally closed]] iff it is formally $M_v$-smooth and proper iff it is formally $M_v$-etale (in the sense of KR 6.3).